gomodel:SYNGO_2687  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Summary: Enriched environment triggers structural synaptic plasticity in the hippocampus that requires beta-adducin.\n\nFig.2: \"Enhanced Synapse Turnover in Mature Organotypic Slice Cultures Lacking β-Adducin\"\n- \"By contrast, β-Adducin-/- LMTs exhibited dramatic remodeling of filopodia and satellites (Figures 2A and 2B), suggesting enhanced synapse turnover in the absence of β-Adducin....reintroduction of GFP-β-Adducin into granule cells restored the stability of satellites and filopodia at LMTs of transduced neurons (Figure 2B).\"\n- \"we monitored spine turnover in the stratum radiatum of hippocampal CA1 in mature wild-type and β-Adducin-/- slice cultures. In the absence of β-Adducin, spine gains and losses were more than twice as frequent as in wild-type cultures (Figures 2C and 2D)\" ...\"we reintroduced the protein into CA1. The GFP-β-Adducin construct ...completely restored spine stability (Figure 2D).\"\n\nFig.3: \"Specific Increase in AZ Lability, but No Alterations in Synapse Numbers in β-Adducin-/- Mice Housed under Control Conditions\"\n\nFig.4: \"Synapse Disassembly in Enriched Mice Depends on phosphorylation of β-Adducin Involving PKC\"\n\nFig.5: \"Failure to Increase Synapse, but Not Thorn Numbers at LMTs upon Enrichment in Mice Lacking β-Adducin\"\n\nFig.6: \"Failure to Increase Synapse, but Not Spine Numbers in CA1 upon Enrichment in Mice Lacking β-Adducin\"\n\nModel: Fig.8 \"Relationship between Learning, Environmental Enrichment, and Connectivity Rearrangements in the Adult\"\n\nDiscussion: \"We have shown that mice lacking β-Adducin have a specific deficit to assemble new synapses under conditions of enhanced plasticity\"\n\nNote: I did not select the \"regulation of...\" version of the 'synapse assembly (GO:0007416)' term because of the known role of beta-adducin as a F-actin capping protein.. Experimental description: - \"β-Adducin-/- mice (B6.129-β-Adducintm1Feb/Ibcm; Gilligan et al., 1999) were generously provided ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2687" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

